news.title: Dubai developer Union Properties says $42 million 'misappropriated'
news.para: The announcement by Union Properties comes as Emirati prosecutors announced in October they were investigating the firm. Already, the firm's board of directors has seen its chairmen and other officials dismissed amid the probe.

news.title: Explained: What Supertech's bankruptcy means for its home buyers
news.para: Supertech Ltd, which is planning to challenge the order in the National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT), said the projects under the company have 38,041 units, of which 27,111 homes have been delivered.

news.title: About 1.15 crore houses sanctioned under PMAY-Urban; CLSS ending this month
news.para: ​Replying to supplementary questions of members, the minister said the government, based on the assessment demands provided by states, has sanctioned 1.15 crore houses under PMAY-U which ends in March 2022, and various projects underway will be completed in the next 18 months or so.

news.title: Godrej Properties has a war chest of $1 billion, will like to enter new cities now: MD
news.para: “We would like to enter new cities now. We are already amongst the top players in the top four cities and we intend to enter new cities in India. Sonipat is the first city in line of that strategy. For our new cities, the strategy is we would like to do plotted developments or low rise developments.”

news.title: Delhi government should hand over 35,000 flats built under RRAY in 2007-10: Centre
news.para: The Rajiv Ratan Awas Yojana (RRAY) is a centrally-sponsored scheme, implemented between 2007 and 2010, by the then Delhi government as part of the Jawaharlal Nehru Urban Rehabilitation Mission.

news.title: Allegations made in NCLT petition downright untruthful: Max Group Chairman
news.para: "Apart from being downright untruthful, what is even more anguishing is the agenda with which these reports have been encouraged and planted while the matter is sub judice," said a statement put on BSE by Max quoting Analjit Singh.

news.title: Mumbai's police commissioner gives builders till March 31 to put sound screens
news.para: Pandey has warned contractors, builders, and developers of stern action if they fail to take this anti-noise pollution measure. So far, two developers and three labourers have been fined under the Bombay Police Act for noise pollution.

news.title: Bengaluru: Stamps & registration revenue beats target this fiscal
news.para: As against a target of Rs 11,150 crore for April-February, the state collected Rs 12,229.3 crore from stamps and registration, official data given as part of a written reply in the legislative council shows.

news.title: Pune: PMC sealing civic properties over rent dues in fresh drive
news.para: At least 27 such commercial properties have already been sealed to recover dues worth Rs3.5 crore. According to PMC data, it has over 3,700 properties that have been given out on rent across city localities.

news.title: Delhi: NDMC to revamp three housing complexes
news.para: To begin with, NDMC has finalised a scheme for repairing houses and common areas in three societies for municipal sanitation staff — Balmiki Basti housing complex (Mandir Marg), costing Rs.7.5 crore; Palika Dham Housing Complex, Gole Market (Rs 4.5 crore); and housing Complex Bapu Dham, Chanakyapuri (Rs 1 crore).

news.title: Chandigarh civic body to dispose of 200 properties worth over Rs 200 crore
news.para: The move comes in the wake of the decision of the Chandigarh administration to convert leasehold properties of all departments and UT authorities for their proper disposal.

news.title: Sagar Cements surges 8% as board okays issuance of shares to Premji Invest affiliate
news.para: The company’s scrip surged to a high of Rs 275 as against Rs 254.85 at previous close on the National Stock Exchange. The stock was last trading 3 per cent higher.

news.title: Pune civic body eyes revenue from Metro assets by charging property tax
news.para: The civic body is eying revenue generation from Metro stations and pillars, by charging property tax at commercial rates.

news.title: Nashik civic body brings 5 lakh properties into tax net
news.para: The property tax department of the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) brought 4,000 new properties into the tax net in the last 40 days.

news.title: About 48 ready-to-move-in flats to be allotted in Greater Noida
news.para: These are ready-to-move-in one, two and three BHK flats located in Sector Omicron 1 & 1 A, MU 2, XU 3, Eta 2 and Sector 12. The houses are in the range of Rs 9 lakh to Rs 73 lakh – with varied prices according to the sector.
